You could use [@Profile][1] annotation on your implementations. It will load a bean only if specified profile/s are currently active.
```
@Component
@Profile({&quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;})
public IImplementationCore implements YourInterface {
}
```
Specify the profiles for test implementation the same way.

If this test class is very specific, like being the only one needing implementation core, you can use [@ActiveProfiles][2] on it to activate profile different from current for this test class only.
```
//other annotations
@ActiveProfiles(&quot;a&quot;)
public TestClass {
}
```


